 and required system properties, I have to consider the question of necessary setups for meaningful coverage.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying advisory preparation**\\n\\nI think the action should be advisory preparation. I need to ensure the JSON is valid and structured as a single object. There are risks to consider, like the optional OAuth2 class requiring an extra dependency if tests choose to use OAuth2, which should be avoided unless absolutely necessary. Also, properties are specific to Native Image under JDK25/Netty, so I should be careful not to mask important metadata. \\n\\nI’ll note that there’s no deterministic setup and summarize that the generated or updated `build.gradle` must keep the local loopback HttpServer and the runtime args for library version 5.0.1 or 5.0.x. The user has specifically requested not to modify the repository or apply any setups themselves — just a decision in JSON is all that's needed.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating native-image run issue**\\n\\nIt seems that meaningful coverage under authoritative native verification isn't achievable unless it passes. I’m considering whether using `-Dio.netty.noUnsafe=true` could be a better option to avoid unsafe scenarios, but the existing repo leverages an allow/tryReflection pattern, so we might want to stick with that. I think `-Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow` is a runtime property that could apply, possibly a Java 25 flag?\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra Maven dependency or Docker service is needed for meaningful Vert.x Web Client coverage; normal usage is an in-process Vert.x WebClient talking to an HTTP server. However, vertx-web-client 5.0.1 resolves Netty 4.2.2.Final, and the existing 5.0.0 scaffold already documents that Netty 4.2.x needs explicit unsafe-access runtime properties on Java 25 native runs.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Keep tests self-contained with a loopback Vert.x HttpServer. In the test build, extend the existing nativeTest runtimeArgs setup for Vert.x 5.0.x / libraryVersion == '5.0.1' to include '-Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow' and '-Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true'. Do not add external services. Avoid OAuth2WebClient coverage unless intentionally adding the optional io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2 dependency in test scope.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"OAuth2WebClient is part of the public API but depends on optional vertx-auth-oauth2; tests that import or exercise OAuth2 support will need an explicit test dependency.\",\n    \"The system properties address the known Netty 4.2.x / Java 25 native runtime requirement; local Gradle and Native Image verification may still expose missing reachability metadata that must be fixed separately.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0bf84645d7061043016a4069d2f11c819389b508952088eb8f\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1326, "output": 1267, "cacheRead": 27136, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29729, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782606278250, "responseId": "resp_0bf84645d7061043016a4069c6db5081939d7cb4f815183519"}, "toolResults": []}
